1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with space-time coding for wireless relay networks, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of a wireless relay network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new class of distributed space-time block codes, which can be seen as a control system for the relay network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of complex vectors, which can be considered as a form of multimedia data. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the societal impact of wireless relay networks and their design.
